<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<link rel="shortcut icon" href="../assets/en/img/img_32.ico" type="image/x-icon" />
		<meta name="description" content="Netflix Statistics English" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>Netflix Statistics</title>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<!-- js -->
		<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/countup.js/1.8.2/countUp.min.js"></script>
		<script defer src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/2.9.3/Chart.bundle.js"></script>
		<script defer src="../assets/en/js/convert.js"></script>
		<script defer src="../assets/en/js/index.js"></script>
		<!-- css -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="../assets/en/css/index.css" />
		<!-- analytics -->
		<script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=UA-173567015-1"></script>
		<script>
			window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []
			function gtag() {
				dataLayer.push(arguments)
			}
			gtag("js", new Date())

			gtag("config", "UA-173567015-1")
		</script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="main">
			<div class="one">
				<h1 id="h11">Netflix Statistics</h1>
				<p id="p1">
					Wondering how much time you spent watching Netflix in your life so far? <br />
					If you want to know you have to follow the instructions!
				</p>
				<h2 id="h21">Instructions</h2>
				<p id="p2">
					1. First you need to download your statistics from your Netflix profile.
					<br />
					<a target="_blank" href="https://help.netflix.com/en/node/101917">(Written help)</a>
					<a target="_blank" href="https://www.netflix.com/viewingactivity">Link if your logged in</a>
					<a target="_blank" href="../assets/en/vid/vid_en.mp4">(Video help)</a>
					<br />
					2. Select the file you downloaded below. <br />
					3. If you did everything right just scroll down and you can already see the stats.
				</p>
				<h2 id="h21">Choose the file</h2>
				<input type="file" id="csvFileInput" onchange="handlefiles(this.files)" accept=".csv" />
			</div>

			<div class="two">
				<h1 id="h11">Statistics</h1>
				<p id="p3">Here are your Netflix stats so far. I think you were surprised.</p>
				<h2 id="h21">Viewed titles:</h2>
				<h3 id="h31" class="counter">0</h3>
				<h2>Titles</h2>
				<h2 id="h21">Time spent:</h2>
				<div class="grid">
					<h3 id="h32" class="counter">0</h3>
					<h3 id="h33" class="counter">0</h3>
					<h3 id="h34" class="counter">0</h3>
					<h2>In minutes</h2>
					<h2>In hours</h2>
					<h2>In days</h2>
				</div>
			</div>

			<canvas id="chart"></canvas>

			<button id="but" onclick="restart()">Clear statistics</button>
		</div>

		<%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>

	</body>
</html>
